            <entry xml:id="entry_daræn" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>daræn</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>стойбище с постройками для скота и пастухов</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>camp with buildings for livestock and shepherds</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="ru">Во второй части сложных слов означает
                        ‘вместилище’: </note>
                    <note type="comment" xml:lang="en">In the second part of compound words, it
                        means 'container': </note>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>cæx-daræn</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>солонка</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>saltcellar</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                    <re>
                        <form type="lemma"><orth>cyraǧ-daræn</orth></form>
                        <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                                <q>подсвечник</q>
                            </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                                <q>candlestick</q>
                            </abv:tr></sense>
                    </re>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Girgol jæ fos ærtardta, īw ræsuǧd ræbynawy daræn ærcaræzta æmæ jæ fos
                            xīzyn rajdydta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Джиргол пригнал свое стадо, устроил %sdaræn%s в живописном (месте) у
                                подножия и стал пасти свое стадо</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Jirgol drove his flock, set up daræn in a picturesque (place) at the
                                foothills and began to graze his flock</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>27</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>fæjjaw jæ daræn aīvta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>пастух переменил стойбище</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>the shepherd changed his camp</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сл."/></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Восходит к <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*dārana-</w></mentioned>; собственно „где держат (%idar%i-) что-либо“;
                    ср. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>darana-</w>
                        <gloss><q>местопребывание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>dharaṇa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>dhāraṇa-</w>
                        <gloss><q>держание</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>держащий</q></gloss></mentioned>. Для значения ‘пастбище’ ср.
                    также <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>dār-</w>
                        <gloss><q>пасти</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w>dārán
                            čárand</w>
                        <gloss><q>они пасут</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>VII 771</biblScope></bibl>). Для значения
                    ‘вместилище’ — <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>daran</w></mentioned> в сложных словах <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>matʼenadaran</w>
                        <gloss><q>книгохранилище</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>matʼean</w>
                        <gloss><q>книга</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>pʼatʼkʼan-daran</w>
                        <gloss><q>колчан</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>p’at’k’an</w>
                        <gloss><q>стрела</q></gloss></mentioned>) (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Arm._Gr."/><biblScope>I 136
                        сл.</biblScope></bibl>). См. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_daryn"/>
                            ‘держать’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">It traces back to <mentioned xml:lang="ira"><lang/>
                        <w>*dārana-</w></mentioned>; basically “where something is kept (%idar%i-)”;
                    cf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>darana-</w>
                        <gloss><q>whereabouts</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/>
                        <w>dharaṇa-</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>dhāraṇa-</w>
                        <gloss><q>keeping</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>one who is keeping</q></gloss></mentioned>. For the meaning
                    ‘pasture’ cf. also <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>dār-</w>
                        <gloss><q>browse</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><w>dārán
                            čárand</w>
                        <gloss><q>they browse</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_BSOS"/><biblScope>VII 771</biblScope></bibl>). For the
                    meaning ‘container’ — <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>daran</w></mentioned> in such compounds as <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>matʼenadaran</w>
                        <gloss><q>book stack</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>matʼean</w>
                        <gloss><q>book</q></gloss></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>pʼatʼkʼan-daran</w>
                        <gloss><q>quiver</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>p’at’k’an</w>
                        <gloss><q>arrow</q></gloss></mentioned>) (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Hübschmann._Arm._Gr."/><biblScope>I 136
                        сл.</biblScope></bibl>). See <ref type="xr" target="#entry_daryn"/>
                            ‘keep’.%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"
                            /><biblScope>58</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
            </entry>
